    <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock screensteps-wrapper--introduction screensteps-wrapper">
  <div id="text-content_9819D963-B294-40AD-A295-3A2900EADFA3" class="text-block-content">
    <p>You can create an online assignment that embeds a document directly from your Google Drive folder. Accepted assignment types are Google documents, sheets, and slides files.</p>
<p>When students open the assignment, Google Drive will create a copy of the file as the student’s submission. Students can make changes per the assignment instructions directly from the Canvas assignment page. When they are ready to submit the assignment, they can submit the assignment. The copied document is also added to the student’s Google Drive folder for the course. </p>
<p>You can also view each student's document copy in SpeedGrader for grading. Submitted assignments are converted to a PDF to show the assignment at the time of submission. If students made any changes to their assignment, they will have to resubmit it for the changes to be visible in SpeedGrader.</p>
<p><strong>Notes:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>You cannot use Google Drive files in an external tool for group assignments.</li>
<li>If you want your assignment to be moderated, you must <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-add-a-moderated-assignment-to-be-graded-by-multiple/ta-p/605" target="_blank">set up the moderated assignment</a> before setting the External Tool submission type. If you need to return to the moderate page after the External Tool is added, open the assignment and add <em>/moderate</em> after the assignment URL.</li>
<li>To learn how to copy Google App LTI assignments to Google Assignments LTI 1.3 assignments, visit Google's article, <a href="https://support.google.com/edu/assignments/answer/9381694?hl=en#zippy=%2Chow-can-i-copy-an-assignment-from-google-apps-lti-to-assignments-lti" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Use Assignments with Canvas</a>.</li>
</ul>
  </div>
</div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="open_assignments" data-step-uuid="1D476810-29C0-4C83-B7F2-3927F6E861B4">
    <h2 id="open_assignments" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Open Assignments</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/002/744/592/original/d307215f-ac43-4193-87a8-298d0931a011.png" srcset="" alt="Open Assignments" height="271" width="169">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_8DB12C32-6C58-4265-B334-CB32AAE6B1C4" class="text-block-content">
    <p>In Course Navigation, click the <strong>Assignments </strong>link.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="add_assignment" data-step-uuid="6FA7AF10-7D5C-4532-92A6-3E074F25A3F6">
